casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Colwell, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Colwell (1996), 74 Ohio St.3d 631.]

*632(No. 95-2005 Submitted January 23, 1996 Decided February 28, 1996.) Joseph T. Deters, Hamilton County Prosecuting Attorney, and William E. Breyer, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellee. Michael Colwell, pro se. Per Curiam.

We affirm the decision of the court of appeals for the reason stated in its entry.1

Judgment affirmed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Wright, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer and Cook, JJ., concur.

. Appellant’s motions to produce/transmit record and to return copies instead of recycling are also denied.
